  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Big-Omega (Ω) Notation — Interactive Demonstration</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 12px; color: #111; background: #f7fbff; }\n    h1 { margin: 6px 0 12px 0; font-size: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 8px 0; line-height: 1.4; }\n    .container { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }\n    .column { background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(20,40,70,0.06); }\n    .left { width: 420px; }\n    .right { flex: 1; min-width: 360px; }\n    label { display:block; margin-top: 8px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; }\n    select, input[type=\"text\"], input[type=\"number\"] { width: 100%; padding: 8px; margin-top:6px; box-sizing: border-box; border-radius:6px; border: 1px solid #d0d7e0; }\n    button { margin-top: 10px; padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 6px; border: none; background: #2b78ff; color: white; cursor: pointer; }\n    button.secondary { background: #e7eefc; color: #1043b9; border: 1px solid #c8ddff; }\n    canvas { width:100%; height:300px; background: linear-gradient(180deg,#ffffff,#f3f8ff); border-radius:6px; display:block; }\n    .result { margin-top: 10px; padding: 10px; background: #f1f9ff; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid #d6ecff; }\n    .code { background:#0f1724; color:#d1e9ff; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; font-family: monospace; font-size:12px; overflow:auto; max-height: 120px; }\n    .small { font-size: 13px; color:#334155 }\n    .legend { display:flex; gap:10px; margin-top:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap }\n    .legend .item { display:flex; gap:6px; align-items:center; font-size:12px }\n    .swatch { width:12px; height:12px; border-radius:2px; display:inline-block }\n    footer { margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:#475569 }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Big-Omega (Ω) Notation — Interactive Demonstration</h1>\n\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"column left\">\n      <p><strong>Definition (informal):</strong> We write f(n) ∈ Ω(g(n)) if there exist constants c > 0 and n0 such that for all n ≥ n0, f(n) ≥ c·g(n). Intuitively: g(n) is a lower bound for f(n) (up to constant factors) for large n.</p>\n\n      <label>Choose a preset function f(n)</label>\n      <select id=\"presetF\">\n        <option value=\"3*n+5\">f(n) = 3n + 5</option>\n        <option value=\"n*n + 100*n\">f(n) = n^2 + 100n</option>\n        <option value=\"Math.log(n)\">f(n) = log n</option>\n        <option value=\"n\">f(n) = n</option>\n        <option value=\"Math.pow(2,n)\">f(n) = 2^n</option>\n        <option value=\"n * Math.sin(n) + n\">f(n) = n·sin(n) + n (oscillating)</option>\n        <option value=\"0.5*n\">f(n) = 0.5n (smaller constant)</option>\n        <option value=\"n * Math.log(n)\">f(n) = n log n</option>\n      </select>\n\n      <label>Choose a candidate g(n) (lower bound)</label>\n      <select id=\"presetG\">\n        <option value=\"n\">g(n) = n</option>\n        <option value=\"n * Math.log(n)\">g(n) = n log n</option>\n        <option value=\"n*n\">g(n) = n^2</option>\n        <option value=\"Math.log(n)\">g(n) = log n</option>\n        <option value=\"1\">g(n) = 1</option>\n        <option value=\"Math.pow(2,n)\">g(n) = 2^n</option>\n      </select>\n\n      <label>Or enter a custom f(n) or g(n) expression (use variable n)</label>\n      <input id=\"customF\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"optional: e.g. 4*n + 10\" />\n      <input id=\"customG\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"optional: e.g. n*n\" style=\"margin-top:6px;\" />\n\n      <label>Range & sampling</label>\n      <div style=\"display:flex; gap:8px;\">\n        <input id=\"nStart\" type=\"number\" value=\"1\" min=\"1\" style=\"width: 80px;\" />\n        <input id=\"nMax\" type=\"number\" value=\"200\" min=\"2\" style=\"width: 110px;\" />\n        <input id=\"sampleStep\" type=\"number\" value=\"1\" min=\"1\" style=\"width: 110px;\" />\n      </div>\n\n      <button id=\"testBtn\">Test Ω relationship (empirical)</button>\n      <button id=\"resetBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Reset presets</button>\n\n      <div id=\"result\" class=\"result\" style=\"display:none;\"></div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <strong>Quick examples & formal proofs</strong>\n        <div class=\"small\" style=\"margin-top:6px;\">\n          <p><strong>Example 1:</strong> f(n)=3n+5 is Ω(n). Proof: choose c = 3 and n0 = 1. For n ≥ 1, 3n+5 ≥ 3n = c·n.</p>\n          <p><strong>Example 2:</strong> f(n)=n^2+100n is Ω(n^2). Proof: for n ≥ 100, n^2+100n ≥ n^2 (so c=1,n0=100 works). Better: for n ≥ 1, n^2+100n ≥ n^2.</p>\n          <p><strong>Counterexample:</strong> f(n)=n is NOT Ω(n^2) because n < c·n^2 for any fixed c>0 when n is large (divide both sides gives 1 < c·n, impossible for all large n unless c=0).</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"column right\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between;\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>Plot of f(n) and c·g(n) (found empirically)</strong>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"text-align:right\" class=\"small\">\n          Controls: zoom axis by changing max n / sampling.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <canvas id=\"plot\" width=\"800\" height=\"300\"></canvas>\n\n      <div class=\"legend\">\n        <div class=\"item\"><span class=\"swatch\" id=\"swF\" style=\"background:#0047b3\"></span> f(n)</div>\n        <div class=\"item\"><span class=\"swatch\" id=\"swG\" style=\"background:#ff6b00\"></span> c·g(n)</div>\n        <div class=\"item\"><span class=\"swatch\" id=\"swAxis\" style=\"background:#94a3b8\"></span> axis/grid</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <strong>What the empirical test does</strong>\n        <p class=\"small\">For each candidate n0 between start and max, the script computes the minimum value of f(n)/g(n) for all sampled n ≥ n0 (within the tested range). If that minimum is positive, we set c to that minimum and report that, on the tested range, f(n) ≥ c·g(n) for all sampled n ≥ n0. This is not a formal proof for all n→∞, but it often finds concrete c and n0 that serve as evidence or a counterexample.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px\">\n        <strong>Function definitions used (JavaScript)</strong>\n        <div class=\"code\" id=\"codeBox\">f(n) = ... ; g(n) = ...</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <footer>Note: This interactive tool uses numeric sampling to suggest Ω relationships. Use formal reasoning for mathematical proofs.</footer>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n    // Utility: create function from expression string safely-ish\n    function makeFunc(expr) {\n      // If blank, return null\n      if (!expr || expr.trim() === \"\") return null;\n      // Replace ^ with ** if user types caret\n      expr = expr.replace(/\\^/g, '**');\n      // Build a function of n. We allow Math.<...> in expression.\n      try {\n        /* eslint-disable no-new-func */\n        const fn = new Function('n', 'if (!isFinite(n) || n<=0) { return NaN; } return ' + expr + ';');\n        // test quickly\n        fn(10);\n        return fn;\n      } catch (e) {\n        return null;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // DOM elements\n    const presetF = document.getElementById('presetF');\n    const presetG = document.getElementById('presetG');\n    const customF = document.getElementById('customF');\n    const customG = document.getElementById('customG');\n    const nStartIn = document.getElementById('nStart');\n    const nMaxIn = document.getElementById('nMax');\n    const sampleStepIn = document.getElementById('sampleStep');\n    const testBtn = document.getElementById('testBtn');\n    const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');\n    const resultBox = document.getElementById('result');\n    const codeBox = document.getElementById('codeBox');\n\n    // Canvas drawing\n    const canvas = document.getElementById('plot');\n    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\n    const W = canvas.width;\n    const H = canvas.height;\n\n    function clearCanvas() {\n      ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H);\n      // background\n      ctx.fillStyle = '#fbfdff';\n      ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);\n    }\n\n    function drawGrid() {\n      ctx.strokeStyle = '#e6eef9';\n      ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n      for (let i=0;i<=8;i++){\n        const y = i*(H/8);\n        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(0,y+0.5); ctx.lineTo(W,y+0.5); ctx.stroke();\n      }\n      for (let i=0;i<=10;i++){\n        const x = i*(W/10);\n        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x+0.5,0); ctx.lineTo(x+0.5,H); ctx.stroke();\n      }\n    }\n\n    function plotFunctions(xs, fs, gs, cVal) {\n      clearCanvas();\n      drawGrid();\n      // compute scale\n      const allVals = fs.concat(gs.map(v => (isFinite(v)?v:NaN)).filter(v=>isFinite(v)));\n      const maxV = Math.max(1, ...allVals.map(v=>Math.abs(v)||0));\n      const margin = 20;\n      const xToPx = (i) => margin + (W-2*margin) * (i/(xs.length-1));\n      const yToPx = (v) => {\n        // plot on log scale if values vary huge? Provide linear but clamp negative values at bottom.\n        const vmax = maxV;\n        const scaled = (vmax - Math.max(0, v)) / vmax; // invert so larger v is top\n        return margin + (H-2*margin) * scaled;\n      };\n\n      // Draw axis labels (min, max)\n      ctx.fillStyle = '#334155';\n      ctx.font = '12px system-ui';\n      ctx.fillText('n min: ' + xs[0], 8, H-6);\n      ctx.fillText('n max: ' + xs[xs.length-1], 90, H-6);\n      ctx.fillText('value max ≈ ' + Math.round(maxV*100)/100, W-150, H-6);\n\n      // Plot f(n)\n      ctx.beginPath();\n      ctx.strokeStyle = '#0047b3';\n      ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n      for (let i=0;i<xs.length;i++){\n        const x = xToPx(i);\n        let yv = fs[i];\n        if (!isFinite(yv)) continue;\n        const y = yToPx(yv);\n        if (i===0) ctx.moveTo(x,y); else ctx.lineTo(x,y);\n      }\n      ctx.stroke();\n\n      // Plot c*g(n)\n      ctx.beginPath();\n      ctx.strokeStyle = '#ff6b00';\n      ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n      ctx.setLineDash([6,4]);\n      for (let i=0;i<xs.length;i++){\n        const x = xToPx(i);\n        let yv = gs[i] * cVal;\n        if (!isFinite(yv)) continue;\n        const y = yToPx(yv);\n        if (i===0) ctx.moveTo(x,y); else ctx.lineTo(x,y);\n      }\n      ctx.stroke();\n      ctx.setLineDash([]);\n      // Draw legends small circles\n      ctx.fillStyle = '#0047b3'; ctx.fillRect(8,8,12,12);\n      ctx.fillStyle = '#ff6b00'; ctx.fillRect(8,28,12,12);\n      // horizontal baseline\n      ctx.strokeStyle = '#94a3b8';\n      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(0,H-0.5); ctx.lineTo(W,H-0.5); ctx.stroke();\n    }\n\n    function evaluateOnRange(f, g, nStart, nMax, step) {\n      const xs = [];\n      const fs = [];\n      const gs = [];\n      for (let n = nStart; n <= nMax; n += step) {\n        xs.push(n);\n        try {\n          const fv = f(n);\n          fs.push(Number(fv));\n        } catch(e) { fs.push(NaN); }\n        try {\n          const gv = g(n);\n          gs.push(Number(gv));\n        } catch(e) { gs.push(NaN); }\n      }\n      return { xs, fs, gs };\n    }\n\n    function findOmegaConstants(xs, fs, gs) {\n      // Attempt to find c > 0 and n0 index so that for all i >= idx, fs[i] >= c * gs[i]\n      // We'll search idx from 0..last-1 and compute min ratio = min_i fs[i]/gs[i] for i>=idx where gs[i]>0\n      const len = xs.length;\n      const eps = 1e-12;\n      for (let idx = 0; idx < len; idx++) {\n        let minRatio = Infinity;\n        let valid = true;\n        for (let j = idx; j < len; j++) {\n          const fv = fs[j], gv = gs[j];\n          if (!isFinite(fv) || !isFinite(gv) || gv <= 0) { valid = false; break; }\n          const r = fv / gv;\n          if (!isFinite(r)) { valid = false; break; }\n          if (r < minRatio) minRatio = r;\n        }\n        if (!valid) continue;\n        if (minRatio > eps) {\n          // found a candidate: c = minRatio, n0 = xs[idx]\n          return { found: true, c: minRatio, n0: xs[idx], idx };\n        }\n      }\n      return { found: false };\n    }\n\n    function prettyNumber(x) {\n      if (!isFinite(x)) return String(x);\n      if (x === 0) return '0';\n      if (Math.abs(x) < 1e-4 || Math.abs(x) > 1e6) return x.toExponential(3);\n      return Math.round(x*1000)/1000;\n    }\n\n    function updateCodeBox(fExpr, gExpr) {\n      codeBox.textContent = 'f(n) = ' + fExpr + ' ; g(n) = ' + gExpr;\n    }\n\n    // Initial draw\n    clearCanvas(); drawGrid();\n\n    testBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      // Prepare expressions\n      const fExpr = customF.value.trim() || presetF.value;\n      const gExpr = customG.value.trim() || presetG.value;\n\n      const fFunc = makeFunc(fExpr);\n      const gFunc = makeFunc(gExpr);\n\n      if (!fFunc) { alert('Invalid f(n) expression. Use variable n and JavaScript Math functions (e.g., Math.log).'); return; }\n      if (!gFunc) { alert('Invalid g(n) expression. Use variable n and JavaScript Math functions (e.g., Math.log).'); return; }\n\n      const nStart = Math.max(1, Math.floor(Number(nStartIn.value) || 1));\n      let nMax = Math.floor(Number(nMaxIn.value) || 200);\n      const step = Math.max(1, Math.floor(Number(sampleStepIn.value) || 1));\n      if (nMax <= nStart) { alert('n max must be greater than n start.'); return; }\n      if (nMax - nStart > 20000) { if (!confirm('Large range may be slow. Continue?')) return; }\n\n      updateCodeBox(fExpr, gExpr);\n\n      // Evaluate\n      const { xs, fs, gs } = evaluateOnRange(fFunc, gFunc, nStart, nMax, step);\n\n      // Compute ratios and attempt to find c and n0\n      const res = findOmegaConstants(xs, fs, gs);\n\n      // Display result\n      resultBox.style.display = 'block';\n      if (res.found) {\n        resultBox.innerHTML =\n          '<strong>Empirical result:</strong> Found constants that satisfy f(n) ≥ c·g(n) for all tested n ≥ n0.<br>' +\n          'Suggested c = <strong>' + prettyNumber(res.c) + '</strong>, n0 = <strong>' + res.n0 + '</strong> (checked on sample range).<br>' +\n          '<div style=\"margin-top:6px;\" class=\"small\">This means: on the tested finite range, f(n) ∈ Ω(g(n)) with those constants. For a formal proof you must show the inequality holds for all sufficiently large n.</div>';\n      } else {\n        resultBox.innerHTML =\n          '<strong>No constant c > 0 and sample index n0 found on the tested range.</strong><br>' +\n          '<div style=\"margin-top:6px;\" class=\"small\">Either f(n) does not dominate g(n) (i.e., not Ω(g)), or the required n0 is outside the tested interval, or g(n) is nonpositive for some sampled n.</div>';\n      }\n\n      // For plotting, choose cVal = res.c if found, otherwise cVal = 1 (draw g for comparison)\n      const cVal = res.found ? res.c : 1;\n      plotFunctions(xs, fs, gs, cVal);\n    });\n\n    resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      customF.value = '';\n      customG.value = '';\n      presetF.selectedIndex = 0;\n      presetG.selectedIndex = 0;\n      nStartIn.value = 1;\n      nMaxIn.value = 200;\n      sampleStepIn.value = 1;\n      resultBox.style.display = 'none';\n      updateCodeBox(presetF.value, presetG.value);\n      clearCanvas(); drawGrid();\n    });\n\n    // Initialize code box\n    updateCodeBox(presetF.value, presetG.value);\n\n    // Small convenience: update presets into custom fields on change\n    presetF.addEventListener('change', ()=> {\n      customF.value = '';\n      updateCodeBox(presetF.value, customG.value || presetG.value);\n    });\n    presetG.addEventListener('change', ()=> {\n      customG.value = '';\n      updateCodeBox(customF.value || presetF.value, presetG.value);\n    });\n\n    // Provide some quick auto-run example when page loads\n    window.addEventListener('load', ()=> {\n      // Plot default\n      const defaultF = makeFunc(presetF.value);\n      const defaultG = makeFunc(presetG.value);\n      const { xs, fs, gs } = evaluateOnRange(defaultF, defaultG, 1, 200, 1);\n      const res = findOmegaConstants(xs, fs, gs);\n      const cVal = res.found ? res.c : 1;\n      plotFunctions(xs, fs, gs, cVal);\n    });\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
